    <div class="AssessmentProblem.type">RestrictedConstructedResponse</div>
    <div class="AssessmentProblem.statement"><p>A school is planning a picnic for 90 sixth-grade&#xA0;students. The organizers estimated that students prefer&#xA0;hamburgers to hot dogs in a ratio of 5 to 4.</p>

<p>To have one hamburger or hot dog for each student, how many of each should they order? Explain or show your reasoning. If you get stuck, consider drawing a double number line, table, or&#xA0;tape diagram.<presentation-tag data-tag-title="1 INCH" data-tree-code="MS_pi" data-tree-node-id="243962" data-tree-ref-id="215" src="/presentation_tags/4.tag"></presentation-tag></p>
</div>
